column20: I will be starting at EISCAT on the week of the Kiruna Code Refinery, so I hope to find out the details of the processes and tools that currently in use at EISCAT/IRF and what my colleagues hope to put in place for the EISCAT 3D project in light of attending this course. I'm also curious about the wider community and what, if anything, might be available in the Nordic academic community. Maintaining version control, bug tracking, code review, automated testing, etc. infrastructure is a real task in itself and I'm curious if there is anyway of sharing that as we only have a small team at EISCAT and don't have time for everything. But that might be a foolish notion.
